snippet.textDisplay:
Eddie Hearn is a major hypocrite. As is his boy Joshua. Both of them called Tyson Fury 'boring' for his genuine masterclass in dismantling a fighter of the calibre of Klitschko, just before Klitschko was past his best as when Joshua fought him (and, even then, that fight could've went either way). Now fast forward, Joshua is demolished by Andy Ruiz at his preferred weight, but then in the rematch does what was a fairly bad imitation of Fury against not a fighter of the calibre of Klitschko or Deontay Wilder, but rather an Andy Ruiz who has, for reasons known only to himself, decided to not prepare for this fight and come in way above a competitive fighting weight. And at no point in the fight did Joshua hurt Ruiz. In fact, go back and watch it - every time there was a modicum of an exchange or a hint of a 'fire fight', Ruiz looked better.

Joshua isn't even in the same league as Tyson Fury and Deontay Wilder, which is why you'll never see a unification bout between any of those two and Joshua. Hearn will go back to what his plan was before: have Joshua fight bums like Big Baby Miller and other easy pay day brand-building shite. Then he can go and enjoy his hundreds of millions, with him professing to care about his African heritage while being a proud 'Member of the British Empire', one of the great criminal enterprises in human history, boxing in and thus normalising kleptocracies and vicious totalitarian states like Saudi, all the while breaking the bank balance of Tory scumbags like the Hearn Dynasty.
